# Environment Variables Configuration

This file documents all environment variables required for LogLens.

## Required Environment Variables

### WorkOS Authentication (REQUIRED)
```bash
# WorkOS Client ID - Get from https://dashboard.workos.com/
WORKOS_CLIENT_ID=your_workos_client_id_here

# WorkOS API Key - Get from https://dashboard.workos.com/
# CRITICAL: Never commit this to version control
WORKOS_API_KEY=your_workos_api_key_here

# WorkOS Redirect URI - Must match your deployment URL
# Local: http://localhost:3000/api/auth/callback
# Production: https://yourdomain.com/api/auth/callback
WORKOS_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:3000/api/auth/callback

# WorkOS Cookie Password - Must be at least 32 characters
# Generate with: openssl rand -base64 32
WORKOS_COOKIE_PASSWORD=generate_a_secure_32_character_password_here
```

### Application Configuration (OPTIONAL)
```bash
# Application Base URL
# Local: http://localhost:3000
# Production: https://yourdomain.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Node Environment
# Options: development | production | test
NODE_ENV=development
```

### Analytics & Monitoring (OPTIONAL)
```bash
# Vercel Analytics (if deploying to Vercel)
NEXT_PUBLIC_VERCEL_ANALYTICS_ID=

# Custom Analytics/Monitoring
NEXT_PUBLIC_ANALYTICS_KEY=
```

## Environment Setup Instructions

### Local Development
1. Copy this file to `.env.local`:
   ```bash
   cp .env.example .env.local
   ```

2. Fill in your WorkOS credentials from https://dashboard.workos.com/

3. Generate a secure cookie password:
   ```bash
   openssl rand -base64 32
   ```

### Production Deployment
1. **NEVER** commit `.env.local` or `.env.production` to Git
2. Set environment variables in your deployment platform:
   - **Vercel**: Project Settings → Environment Variables
   - **Netlify**: Site Settings → Environment Variables
   - **Railway**: Project → Variables
   - **AWS/GCP**: Use Secrets Manager or Parameter Store

3. Ensure `WORKOS_REDIRECT_URI` matches your production domain

## Security Notes

⚠️ **CRITICAL SECURITY REQUIREMENTS**:
- Never commit `.env*` files to version control
- Use different WorkOS projects for development and production
- Rotate API keys if they are ever exposed
- Use strong, unique cookie passwords (32+ characters)
- Enable WorkOS security features (MFA, SSO) in production

## Validation Checklist

Before deploying, verify:
- [ ] All required environment variables are set
- [ ] `WORKOS_REDIRECT_URI` matches your deployment URL
- [ ] Cookie password is at least 32 characters
- [ ] No secrets are committed to Git
- [ ] Production uses separate WorkOS project from development
